14
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
14
15
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
15
16
A. Effective July 1, 2026, each full-time and part-time
16
17
employee, including temporary and other limited-term employees, of
17
18
the state who was employed by the state on the last working day of
18
19
June 2026 shall be awarded an annualized salary increase equal to
19
20
five percent (5%) of the employee’s annualized salary as of June 30,
20
21
2026.
21
22
B. As used in this section, “temporary and other limited-term
22
23
employees” are those persons who:
23
24
1. Are not full-time or permanent employees;
24
Req. No. 2706 Page 1

1
2. Are not otherwise excluded by this section; and
1
2
3. Are compensated by an agency, board, commission, or other
2
3
department or other employing entity for a limited duration and
3
4
without any subjective expectation by either the employer or the
4
5
employee that the employment will become permanent.
5
6
C. Employees eligible for the increase provided for in this
6
7
section who are on leave without pay on July 1, 2026, shall receive
7
8
an annualized increase, effective upon their return to work, but
8
9
shall not receive any increase for a period of time prior to their
9
10
return to work.
10
11
